{{Infobox person | name = Hiroyuki Nishimoto | image = | imagesize = | caption = | birthname = | birth_date = {{Birth date|1927|1|3|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Tokyo]], Japan | death_date = {{Death date and age|2015|4|19|1927|1|3|df=y}} | death_place = | othername = | occupation = [[Actor]], [[Voice acting in Japan|voice actor]] | yearsactive = 1950s–2015 | spouse = | domesticpartner = | website = }} {{nihongo|'''Hiroyuki Nishimoto'''|西本裕行|Nishimoto Hiroyuki|3 January 1927 – 19 April 2015}} was a Japanese actor. He began acting in the theatre company [[Bungakuza]] and later co-founded Gekidan Kumo (劇団雲; Theatre Company Gekidan) in 1963. Nishimoto then joined [[Theatre Company Subaru]] in 1976. He provided the voice of [[Snufkin]] in the television adaptions of ''[[Moomin]]'', a book series and comic strip by [[Tove Jansson]]. Nishimoto was also known for dubbing the Japanese language versions of many Disney films. He died of an aortic dissection in 2015, aged 88.<ref>{{cite news|title=Moomin's Snufkin Voice Actor Hiroyuki Nishimoto Passes Away|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-04-21/moomin-snufkin-voice-actor-hiroyuki-nishimoto-passes-away/.87338|accessdate=1 May 2015|publisher=Anime News Network|date=21 April 2015}}</ref>
