===2008 (2 bombings)=== {| class="wikitable" |- ! Name !! Date !! Location !! Dead !! Injured !! Notes |- | [[2008 Dimona suicide bombing|Dimona bombing]] || February 4, 2008 || [[Dimona]] || 1 || 9 || The Damascus leadership of [[Hamas]] claimed responsibility,<ref>{{cite web|last=Toronto|first=Nathan W.|url=https://www.ict.org.il/Article.aspx?ID=1031|title=Where Have All the Bombers Gone?|work=[[Interdisciplinary Center Herzliya]]|date=2008-04-20|accessdate=2016-09-23}}</ref> but it has been argued they knew nothing of it, and that the operation was undertaken at the initiative of Hamas leaders in Gaza.<ref>[[Scott Atran]], 'Who Becomes a terrorist Today?,' in C. Webel, John A. Arnaldi (eds.), [https://books.google.com/books?id=kVJdAQAAQBAJ&pg=PT58 ''The Ethics and Efficacy of the Global War on Terrorism: Fighting Terror with Terror,''] Springer, 2011 p.51.</ref> |- | [[Kerem Shalom suicide bombing]] || April 19, 2008 || [[Kerem Shalom]] border crossing, Gaza Strip || none || 13 || Three Palestinian suicide bombers broke through the border fence to attack the Kerem Shalom IDF post, blowing themselves up and wounding several Israeli soldiers. [[Hamas]] claimed responsibility. |}
