'''Sheikh Umar Aliye''', popularly known as '''Gelemsiyyi''', was an Islamic religious leader in [[Gelemso]], [[Ethiopia]].<ref name="ReferenceA">[http://www.addisadmassnews.com/Bahl/news_item.asp?NewsID=779 አዲስ አድማስ ጋዜጣ፣ ሐምሌ 11፣ 2001፣ የጥበብ ሸማኔዎች (ሱፊዎች በሐረርጌ)]{{dead link|date=May 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

He was another key figure in the Islamization of the [[Ittu Oromo]] and a father of [[Mohammed Zakir Meyra]] and many more heroes and scholars. Perhaps, he is the most widely known scholar, activist and important Islam figure in the region. In fact, he is well known for his dedication for Islam and its teaching throughout the country.  He is also the most noted figure in the transmission of the [[Qadiriyyah]] Sufi brotherhood ([[Tariqa]]), which he introduced to the Harar Oromos with [[Sheikh Mohammed Harar]], his close friend with whom he returned from Wallo after the completion of higher education.<ref name="BRAUK">Ulrich Braukämper: ''Islamic History and Culture in Southern Ethiopia. Collected Essays'', Göttinger Studien zur Ethnologie 9, 2003, {{ISBN|978-3-8258-5671-7}}, p. 138, 118& 122, 166, 135, (16-19, 23, 28, 36, 102, 107, 109, 120, 136), (16-19, 23, 28, 36, 102, 107, 109, 120, 136), 117-122, 116, 118, 119, 119, 119, 116-117, (16-19, 23, 28, 36, 102, 107, 109, 120, 136), 131, 118, 70-76, 116-120,- Professor Urlich Braukamper is one of the leading authorities in the study of Islamic History and Culture in Ethiopia.</ref><ref name="jambo.africa.kyoto-u.ac.jp">[http://jambo.africa.kyoto-u.ac.jp/kiroku/asm_suppl/abstracts/pdf/ASM_s41/10.Hussein.pdf Hussein Ahmed ''HARAR-WALLO RELATIONS REVISITED: HISTORICAL, RELIGIOUS AND CULTURAL DIMENSIONS'', African Study Monographs, Kyoto University, March 2010, p. 111-117]</ref> He built the biggest mosque and [[hadira]] (a complex where people are gathering to pray day and night).Sheikh Umar Aliye, popularly known as Gelemsiyyi, was an Islamic religious leader in Gelemso, Ethiopia.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://allchristmasideas.com/podcasts/Sheikh-Umar-Aliye.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-11-13 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131113175240/http://allchristmasideas.com/podcasts/Sheikh-Umar-Aliye.html |archivedate=2013-11-13 |df= }}</ref>

